//! Bytecode interpreter for the Stator VM.
//!
//! This module provides the fetch-decode-dispatch loop that executes
//! [`crate::bytecode::bytecode_array::BytecodeArray`] bytecode.
//!
//! # Overview
//!
//! - [`InterpreterFrame`] О“Г‡Г¶ holds the register file, accumulator,
//!   program counter, and scope context for a single function activation.
//! - [`Interpreter`] О“Г‡Г¶ stateless executor; call [`Interpreter::run`] with
//!   a mutable frame to execute it.
//!
//! # Supported opcodes
//!
//! ## Load / Store
//!
//! | Opcode                 | Semantics                                |
//! |------------------------|------------------------------------------|
//! | `LdaZero`              | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ 0`                                |
//! | `LdaSmi(imm)`          | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ imm`                              |
//! | `LdaUndefined`         | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ undefined`                        |
//! | `LdaNull`              | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ null`                             |
//! | `LdaTrue`              | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ true`                             |
//! | `LdaFalse`             | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ false`                            |
//! | `LdaConstant(k)`       | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ constant_pool[k]`                 |
//! | `Ldar(reg)`            | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ reg`                              |
//! | `Star(reg)`            | `reg О“ГҐГ‰ acc`                              |
//!
//! ## Arithmetic
//!
//! | Opcode                 | Semantics                                |
//! |------------------------|------------------------------------------|
//! | `Add(reg, _)`          | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc + reg`                        |
//! | `Sub(reg, _)`          | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc О“ГЄГ† reg`                        |
//! | `Mul(reg, _)`          | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc в”њГ№ reg`                        |
//! | `Div(reg, _)`          | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc в”њв•– reg`                        |
//! | `Mod(reg, _)`          | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc % reg`                        |
//! | `Inc(_)`               | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc + 1`                          |
//! | `Dec(_)`               | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc О“ГЄГ† 1`                          |
//!
//! ## Comparison
//!
//! | Opcode                    | Semantics                             |
//! |---------------------------|---------------------------------------|
//! | `TestEqual(reg, _)`       | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc == reg`  (abstract eq)    |
//! | `TestNotEqual(reg, _)`    | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc != reg`  (abstract neq)   |
//! | `TestEqualStrict(reg, _)` | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc === reg` (strict eq)      |
//! | `TestLessThan(reg, _)`    | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc < reg`                    |
//! | `TestGreaterThan(reg, _)` | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc > reg`                    |
//! | `TestLessThanOrEqual(r,_)`| `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc <= reg`                   |
//! | `TestGreaterThanOrEqual`  | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc >= reg`                   |
//! | `TestNull`                | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc === null`                 |
//! | `TestUndefined`           | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ acc === undefined`            |
//!
//! ## Logical / Boolean
//!
//! | Opcode                 | Semantics                                |
//! |------------------------|------------------------------------------|
//! | `LogicalNot`           | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ !acc` (boolean-only)              |
//! | `ToBooleanLogicalNot`  | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ !ToBoolean(acc)`                  |
//!
//! ## Control flow
//!
//! | Opcode                    | Semantics                                              |
//! |---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
//! | `Jump(offset)`            | unconditional forward/backward jump                   |
//! | `JumpLoop(offset,О“Г‡ВЄ)`      | back-edge jump (loop repeat)                          |
//! | `JumpIfTrue(offset)`      | jump if `acc === true`                                |
//! | `JumpIfFalse(offset)`     | jump if `acc === false`                               |
//! | `JumpIfToBooleanTrue`     | jump if `ToBoolean(acc)` is truthy                    |
//! | `JumpIfToBooleanFalse`    | jump if `ToBoolean(acc)` is falsy                     |
//! | `JumpIfNull(offset)`      | jump if `acc === null`                                |
//! | `JumpIfNotNull(offset)`   | jump if `acc !== null`                                |
//! | `JumpIfUndefined(offset)` | jump if `acc === undefined`                           |
//! | `JumpIfNotUndefined`      | jump if `acc !== undefined`                           |
//! | `JumpIfUndefinedOrNull`   | jump if `acc === null \|\| acc === undefined`          |
//! | `Return`                  | halt; return `acc`                                    |
//!
//! ## Closure creation
//!
//! | Opcode                    | Semantics                                              |
//! |---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
//! | `CreateClosure(k,_,_)`    | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ Function(constant_pool[k])`                    |
//!
//! ## Function calls
//!
//! | Opcode                       | Semantics                                           |
//! |------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
//! | `CallAnyReceiver(f,a,n,_)`   | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ f(a, a+1, О“Г‡ВЄ, a+nО“ГЄГ†1)` (undefined receiver)  |
//! | `CallUndefinedReceiver0(f,_)` | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ f()` (zero args)                            |
//! | `CallUndefinedReceiver1(f,a,_)` | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ f(a)` (one arg)                           |
//! | `CallUndefinedReceiver2(f,a,b,_)` | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ f(a, b)` (two args)                    |
//! | `CallProperty(f,recv,n,_)`   | method call; `this` = `recv`, `n` args after `f`   |
//! | `CallWithSpread(f,a,n,_)`    | same as `CallAnyReceiver` (spread pre-evaluated)   |
//!
//! ## Construct
//!
//! | Opcode                       | Semantics                                           |
//! |------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------|
//! | `Construct(f,a,n,_)`         | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ new f(a, О“Г‡ВЄ, a+nО“ГЄГ†1)` (P3: returns body acc) |
//! | `ConstructWithSpread(f,a,n,_)` | same as `Construct`                               |
//! | `ConstructForwardAllArgs(f,_)` | like `Construct` but forward all current-frame args |
//!
//! ## Context management
//!
//! | Opcode                    | Semantics                                              |
//! |---------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
//! | `PushContext(reg)`        | `reg О“ГҐГ‰ old_ctx; ctx О“ГҐГ‰ acc`                           |
//! | `PopContext(reg)`         | `ctx О“ГҐГ‰ reg`                                           |
//!
//! ## Exception handling
//!
//! | Opcode      | Semantics                                                          |
//! |-------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|
//! | `Throw`     | throw `acc`; walk handler table, jump to handler or propagate up  |
//! | `ReThrow`   | re-throw `acc`; same dispatch logic as `Throw`                    |
//!
//! ## Generators / Async
//!
//! | Opcode                       | Semantics                                                   |
//! |------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|
//! | `SuspendGenerator(О“Г‡ВЄ)`        | yield `acc`; save registers + PC; exit loop via `suspend_result` |
//! | `ResumeGenerator(О“Г‡ВЄ)`         | restore registers from `GeneratorState`; acc = sent value   |
//! | `GetGeneratorState(gen)`     | `acc О“ГҐГ‰ generator.status` as Smi (О“ГЄГ†2/О“ГЄГ†1/0/1)                |
//! | `SetGeneratorState(gen)`     | `generator.status О“ГҐГ‰ acc` (Smi)                              |
//! | `SwitchOnGeneratorState(gen)`| jump to `resume_pc` if generator was previously suspended   |
//!
//! Generator execution is driven by [`Interpreter::run_generator_step`], which
//! attaches a [`GeneratorState`] to the frame and interprets the body until a
//! `SuspendGenerator` or `Return` instruction is reached.
//!
//! Async functions desugar to generators: each `await` compiles to a `yield`,
//! and the caller of `run_generator_step` plays the role of the microtask
//! queue, resolving awaited values by passing them as the `input` argument.
//!
//! ## Jump-offset encoding
//!
//! Jump offsets are **byte deltas** relative to the byte following the jump
//! instruction.  Positive values jump forward; negative values jump backward.
//! At runtime the interpreter pre-computes a byte-offset table for all
//! instructions and uses binary search to convert a target byte offset back to
//! an instruction index.
//!
//! # Register layout
//!
//! The [`InterpreterFrame`] register file is a flat inline-buffered register
//! file:
//!
//! ```text
//! [ param[0], param[1], О“Г‡ВЄ, local[0], local[1], О“Г‡ВЄ ]
//! О“Г¶Г©О“ГҐГ‰О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡ parameter_count О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“ГҐГ†О“Г¶Г©О“ГҐГ‰О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡ frame_size О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“Г¶Г‡О“ГҐГ†О“Г¶Г©
//! ```
//!
//! Bytecode operands encode register indices as `u32` using a two's-complement
//! bit-cast of the compiler's `i32` register index:
//!
//! - `v as i32 >= 0` О“Г‡Г¶ local or temporary register; flat index =
//!   `parameter_count + v`.
//! - `v as i32 < 0`  О“Г‡Г¶ parameter register; flat index = `-(v as i32 + 1)`.
//!
//! # Dispatch strategy
//!
//! Instructions are pre-decoded once by
//! [`crate::bytecode::bytecodes::decode_with_byte_offsets`] into a
//! `Vec<Instruction>` and a parallel byte-offset table.  The main loop fetches
//! one [`Instruction`] per iteration, advances the program counter, then
//! dispatches on the [`Opcode`] via an exhaustive `match`.

